<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Australia-Population     11-21 0131</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Australia-Population,0134</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Biggest Annual Increase Since 1950 Recorded</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CANBERRA, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The country's population grew by
268,600 in the past year to total 16.5 million, its biggest annual
increase since 1950, the Bureau of Statistics said.
   The year that ended June 30 was also just the third since 1950 in
which net migration exceeded natural increase _ the excess of births
over deaths _ in total population growth, the bureau said Monday.
   The Bureau of Statistics said net migration _ permanent arrivals
minus departures _ totalled 143,200, also the largest increase since
1949-1950.
   It said Britain and New Zealand were the largest source of
migrants, followed by the Philippines, Malayasia, Vietnam and Hong
Kong.
   Aborigines, the country's indigenous inhabitants, number some
160,000, or about 1 percent of Australia's population.
</TEXT>
