<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0508</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Wet, Windy Weather in North</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Snow fell over sections of New England, the Midwest and the West
today, with Maine braced for up to 8 inches of snow, and gale
warnings were in effect along parts of both coasts and the Great
Lakes.
   Snow was falling over northern Maine at midnight Sunday. A winter
storm warning predicted 5 to 8 inches of snow in northern and
mountain sections of the state. Winter weather advisories for 2 to 5
inches were in effect for the rest of inland Maine and northern
Vermont.
   Rain fell over the rest of northern New England and northern New
York state.
   Snow extended from west central Minnesota into east central North
Dakota and from west central Wyoming into eastern Idaho. Scattered
snow fell over northern lower Michigan.
   Scattered rain showers fell over northwest Montana and light rain
fell over Washington state's northern coast.
   Warnings for gale-force winds were in effect for the northern
half of both the East and West coasts, as well as for the lower
Great Lakes and Lake Huron.
   Today's forecast called for rain over the lower Great Lakes, snow
showers from northeast New York state to northern New England, with
rain over the northern New England coast; snow over western Montana,
becoming rain at lower elevations; and rain in the Idaho Panhandle
and the northern two-thirds of the Pacific Coast.
   High temperatures were expected to be in the 30s from southern
Maine to the Great Lakes, the upper Mississippi Valley, North Dakota
and northeast Montana; 40s and 50s from the rest of New England to
New Jersey, the central Appalachians, and the Ohio and Tennessee
valleys, from Iowa and South Dakota to northern Louisiana and
central Texas, from the rest of Montana to the Rockies, and along
the northern two-thirds of the Pacific Coast. The 60s and 70s were
exepcted in the desert Southwest; the 70s along the Georgia Coast
and northern Florida; 80s in the lower two-thirds of Florida; the
60s elsewhere.
   Temperatures around the nation at 2 .a.m. EST ranged from 12
degrees at Rochester, N.Y., to 80 degrees at Homestead and Key West,
Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 46 fair; Boston 50 windy; Buffalo 38 cloudy;
Caribou 29 snow; Charleston, S.C. 61 partly cloudy; Cincinnati 38
cloudy; Cleveland 41 cloudy; Detroit 38 windy; Miami 78 partly
cloudy; New York 50 windy; Philadelphia 50 windy; Pittsburgh 39
drizzle; Portland, Me. 38 drizzle; Washington 53 partly cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 16 foggy; Chicago 32 cloudy; Dallas-Ft. Worth
35 fair; Denver 24 fair; Des Moines 18 fair; Indianapolis 34 cloudy;
Kansas City 26 fair; Mpls-St. Paul 12 foggy; Nashville 40 cloudy;
New Orleans 49 partly cloudy; St. Louis 27 foggy.
   _West: Albuquerque 31 cloudy; Anchorage 32 cloudy; Las Vegas 37
fair; Los Angeles 51 fair; Phoenix 47 fair; Salt Lake City 33
cloudy; San Diego 49 fair; San Francisco 48 fair; Seattle 47 cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 34 cloudy; Toronto 39 cloudy.
</TEXT>
