<HEAD>Boy Goes To Private School After Public School Harassment</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 12-year-old boy started classes at
a private school Monday, eight months after he quit his public
school because he was taunted and beaten by classmates who derided
his dark skin and hair.
   ``It's great to be able to attend school again,'' said Sean
Pagano, a Sephardic Jew, when he arrived at the Liberal Jewish Day
School in West Hempstead, on Long Island, where he was offered a
free education.
   He was welcomed by eight students from the school who were on
board the bus that picked him up.
   ``It's cool that he's here,'' said fellow student Stephanie
Mitchell. ``But it was unfair the way he got here.''
   Pagano has been out kept out of school by his parents since last
March because he was beaten by students in Massapequa who made fun
of his dark skin and jet black hair.
   His story gained attention after Massapequa school officials
threatened to take Pagano's parents to court to force their son to
return to school.
   Headmaster Samuel Briedner said the board of directors at the
Liberal Jewish Day School agreed to waive the $3,700 tuition for
Pagano. But since last week, several people have offered to pay his
way.
   Briedner said most contributions came from non-Jews.
