<HEAD>Two Men Shot To Death; Police Suspect Mafia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PALERMO, Sicily (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gunman opened fire through a car window
and killed two men Monday, and police said they suspected it was a
Mafia killing.
   Giovanni Amato and Michele Virga were driving near Piazza Scaffa
when another auto cut them off and forced them to stop.
   At least one gunman ran to the right-hand window and opened fire
with a .38-caliber pistol, killing the men, police said.
   The assassin's car was found abandoned and burned a few hundred
yards away.
   Police said they suspected the Mafia was involved, noting that
Amato, 67, was under investigation for alleged underworld ties. He
was arrested in March in connection with a fraud investigation, but
was freed pending his trial.
   Virga, 52, had no criminal record, police said.
