<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   The National Guard was patrolling in Tuscaloosa, Ala., as the
South cleaned up today from a barrage of nearly two dozen
late-season tornadoes and storms that killed at least two people and
damaged more than 150 homes.
   The same storm system carried high winds and heavy rains to parts
of Ohio and Pennsylvania on Sunday, ripping off the roof of an empty
school in southwestern Pennsylvania and toppling a 75-foot Christmas
