   A movie glutton's fantasy day:
   Join THE BREAKFAST CLUB for BREAKFAST AT TIFFANY'S. Try the
BANANAS.
   For lunch, a snack, perhaps MYSTIC PIZZA.
   Or, consider a PICNIC or LUNCH ON THE GRASS, with a COLD TURKEY
hero or sandwich. (A HERO AIN'T NOTHING BUT A SANDWICH.)
   Then, of course, DINNER at EIGHT. But where? THE DINER? DINNER AT
THE RITZ? DINNER AT ANDRE'S? Or perhaps A CATERED AFFAIR at ALICE'S
RESTAURANT, or THE STORK CLUB (but don't go WITHOUT RESERVATIONS).
   Other possibilities: THE STAGE DOOR CANTEEN or the CABARET.
   Or, a CLAMBAKE.
   If Chinese food sounds good, try the TEAHOUSE OF THE AUGUST MOON
and trust you won't get BITTER RICE. Bring friends, because WITH SIX
YOU GET EGGROLL. And don't leave without your FORTUNE COOKIE.
   But then, you might prefer ROOM SERVICE.
   Wherever you decide, you might start with LA BONNE SOUPE, or DUCK
SOUP (with ANIMAL CRACKERS), and, if you're really hungry, follow
with BABETTE'S FEAST (blini with black caviar, quail stuffed with
foie gras).
   Skip the corn (you know why).
   For dessert, WILD STRAWBERRIES.
   The result? FAT CITY.
