<HEAD>BC-SPECIAL EDITION</HEAD>
<HEAD>FOOD: Oats</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Samuel Johnson once defined oats as ``a grain, which in England
is generally given to horses, but in Scotland supports the people.''
   Indeed, oats can provide a varied menu.
   The cereal grass is sometimes ground or rolled into meal or
flakes, for oatmeal.
   Or made into a thin, flat oatcake.
   James Walker, managing director of The Walkers Bakery, of
Scotland, says oatcakes have been found to be more nutritional, with
recent studies indicating that eating oat products can reduce
cholesterol and help prevent heart disease.
</TEXT>
