about the size of a microwave oven.
   Dubbed the ``BreakMate,'' the machine dispenses three different
soft drinks into cups in a programmed portion size.
   An on-board carbon dioxide tank turns tap water into carbonated
water, then the machine mixes carbonated water with drink syrup,
chilled by a small refrigeration unit.
