<HEAD>Grand Met Again Extends Pillsbury Offer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MONTVALE, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Grand Metropolitan PLC announced today it
has again extended its $60-a-share all-cash tender offer for the
Pillsbury Co.
   Unless extended again, the offer is now set to expire at midnight
EST Friday, Nov. 25. The offer was to have expired at midnight last
Friday.
   Grand Met now says more than 72 million shares of Pillsbury
common stock, representing about 84.6 percent of outstanding shares,
have been tendered and not withdrawn.
   Grand Met, a British conglomerate, launched a $5.23 billion
takeover bid for Pillsbury last month. The board of the
Minneapolis-based restaurant and food company has urged rejection of
the offer.
   Larry Haeg, director of public relations for Pillsbury, said
today the company has no comment on Grand Met's fourth extension of
the offer.
</TEXT>
