<1ST_LINE>r f BC-WeeklySteel     11-21 0145</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Weekly Steel,0146</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Steel Output Fell 3 Percent in Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Steel production fell to 1.783 million tons in
the week ended Nov. 19, a decrease of 3.0 percent from the previous
week's 1.838 million tons, the American Iron and Steel Institute
reported Monday.
   The industry's production amounted to 83.2 percent of capacity
during the week, compared with 85.7 percent in the previous week.
   Estimated figures for the year to date showed production at
88.205 million net tons, an increase of 14.4 percent from the 77.087
million net tons in the previous year.
   Production so far this year used 89.0 percent of capacity,
compared with 77.7 percent a year earlier.
   Net tonnage by district for the week ended Nov. 19: Northeast
Coast, 264,000; Pittsburgh, 193,000; Youngstown, 99,000; Lake Erie,
122,000; Detroit, 163,000; Chicago, 441,000; Midwest, 187,000;
Southern, 222,000; and Western, 92,000.
</TEXT>
