<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-Disney     11-21 0319</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Disney,0331</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Disney Profit Flat in 4th Qtr., Up 17 Percent for Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BURBANK, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Walt Disney Co. said its
fourth-quarter profit was flat, but that its full-year earnings rose
17 percent, boosted by big-spending theme park patrons and a string
of hit movies.
   Disney reported Monday its profit was $136.4 million, or 99 cents
a share, in the fourth quarter, up marginally from $135.3 million,
or 98 cents a share, in the fourth quarter of 1987.
   Sales for the quarter ended Sept. 30 were $1.01 billion, up 34
percent from $758.6 million a year ago.
   The results of a subsidiary that has since been sold are included
in the figure for fourth-quarter 1987, reducing the
quarter-to-quarter gain. When only continuing operations are
compared, profits were 23 percent higher in the fourth quarter of
1988 than they were a year ago.
   For its entire fiscal year, Disney reported a profit of $522
million, or $3.80 a share, up 17 percent from $444.7 million, or
$3.23 a share, in 1987.
   Sales in fiscal 1988 were $3.44 billion, up 20 percent from $2.88
billion the previous year.
   In Disney's biggest division, theme parks and resorts, year-end
sales were up 11 percent, to $2.04 billion. The company, which
doesn't release attendance figures, said attendance was down from
last year, but that customers spent more.
   The movie and television division, riding high on the popularity
of ``Three Men and a Baby,'' ``Good Morning, Vietnam'' and ``Who
Framed Roger Rabbit,'' recorded a 31 percent gain in sales, to $1.15
billion for the year.
   An expanding string of stores selling Disney-themed toys and
clothes had sales of $84.6 million, up 78 percent from last year,
when far fewer stores were in operation.
   Results from Arvida Corp, a housing developer in Boca Raton,
Fla., that Disney has since sold, are included in both the fourth
quarter and year-end results for last year.

</TEXT>
