<1ST_LINE>r f BC-FordRecall     11-21 0148</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Ford Recall,0154</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Ford Recalls 341,000 Aerostars for Door Problem</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DEARBORN, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Co. on Monday recalled 341,000
1986 and 1987 Aerostar minivans because of a potential problem in a
hinge and the track assemblies on sliding doors.
   Operators of affected minivans may notice that the cargo door
becomes difficult to move and may become jammed and the door may
leave the track in extreme cases, the automaker said.
   Ford said in a news release that the problem does not affect the
vehicle's safety.
   Owners of the affected vehicles will be notified in writing. If
there is a problem, Ford will cover costs of parts and labor and
will reimburse owners who already had work done on the problem.
   The company said about 310,000 of the vehicles were sold in the
United States, 30,000 were sold in Canada and about 950 were sold
elsewhere.
</TEXT>
